      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "I enjoyed ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Fashion Police Squad",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " and its unique take on the FPS genre. It does enough to warrant at least one playthrough, but the swinging sections in the later stages were incredibly frustrating and the short run time left me wanting more. Perhaps if the developer was to ever make a sequel with a more meaty campaign, maybe even thrown in a multiplayer aspect to extend the longevity, it’d fare better. But as it stands, ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 2,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Fashion Police Squad",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": " is a solid game that just needs tightening up a bit.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
